The author expresses concern over the Supreme Court's decision to allow SB8 to remain in effect in Texas. They highlight the significant consequences this law has for women in Texas and across the country, as well as for the rule of law. The author reaffirms their commitment to the constitutional right recognized in Roe v. Wade and acknowledges the need for further action in states where women's rights are under attack. They pledge to continue working with Congress to pass the Women's Health Protection Act and stand with women to protect and defend their constitutional right under Roe v. Wade.